# httpClient block with httpTimeout/httpRetry on JS (js-http-config-namespace-tdz)

`httpTimeout`/`httpRetry` imported from std/http were emitted as a namespace member
that resolved to `undefined` on JS (the identity intrinsic target is shadowed by the
generated namespace `const httpTimeout`), so calling them inside an `httpClient { }`
block threw "not callable: ()". The intrinsics now target non-shadowed `_`-aliases.
This exercises only the config side (no real network I/O), so output is deterministic.

[httpClient, httpTimeout, httpRetry](std/http.ssc)

```scalascript
def main(): Unit =
  httpClient("http://example.invalid") {
    println("inside-block")
    httpTimeout(2000)
    httpRetry(2, 500)
  }
  println("after")
```
